<title>USA: Intel sets guidelines for PC cameras.</title>
<headline>Intel sets guidelines for PC cameras.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA CLARA, Calif. 1997-07-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Intel Corp said Monday it released design guidelines to develop PC cameras to use with Intel-based computers.</p>
<p>The guidelines, meant to overcome current problems such as multiple PC-connectivity alternatives and varying file amd storage formats, are supported by Hewlett-Packard Co, Eastman Kodak Co and Microsoft Corp among others, the company said.</p>
<p>&quot;We believe the use of imaging with PCs will be as common as the use of electronic mail today,&quot; Peter Green, general manager of Intel's digital peripherals division, said in a statement.</p>
